You may NOT copy, modify, distribute, sublicense, or use Enterprise Edition
code except as expressly permitted by a signed GAL Commercial License
Agreement.

Runtime gate: Enterprise Edition code compiles but is functionally INERT
without a valid signed license key, verified through the gal kernel capability
check (gal_license_allows / GAL_CAP_EE_FEATURE). Services, CLI, and dashboard
read the key from environment/secret and self-disable when it is absent.

OSS builds (-tags oss / GAL_OSS=1 / cargo --no-default-features) DROP all
Enterprise Edition code from the artifact entirely. Published OSS packages
therefore contain zero commercial code.

